#Approach:

Majority Element – Boyer Moore Voting Algorithm

Is problem me hume wo element find karna hai jo array me n/2 se zyada baar aata ho.
Iske liye hum Boyer-Moore Voting Algorithm use karte hain.

Hum do variables rakhte hain: count aur candidate element.

Array traverse karte waqt:
Agar count 0 ho jaye, to current element ko candidate bana do aur count = 1 kar do.
Agar current element candidate ke equal ho, to count increase karo.
Agar current element candidate ke equal nahi ho, to count decrease karo.

Is process me majority element kabhi completely cancel nahi hota,
aur end tak candidate variable me majority element bach jata hai.

Last me ek baar manually check kar sakte hain ki candidate actually n/2 se zyada baar aata hai ya nahi.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int majorityElement(int[] nums) {
        int cnt = 0;
        int el = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            if(cnt == 0){
                cnt = 1;
                el = nums[i];
            }
            else if(nums[i] == el){
                cnt++;
            }
            else{
                cnt--;
            }
        }

        //Manual checking
        int cnt1 = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            if(nums[i] == el){
                cnt++;
            }
        }

        if(cnt > nums.length/2){
            return el;
        }
        else{
            return -1;
        }
    }
}
